As for the non-CoH areas.<br>
It has EVERYTHING to do with certain co-ordinates. <br>
<br>
CoH is disable in certain <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Co-ordinates</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> , there is a range for it(in terms of simple x an y, CoH diasable when x==designe co-ordinate &amp;&amp; y==design co-ordinates. <br>
<br>
That is how a NON-CoH area is defined. <br>
<br>
