If you had followed this thread from the beginning you would have known that i posted to answer some people who thought a non coh part of a zone is only dependent on the z-axis, which it isn´t - it´s also dependent on the x/y - coordinates. How you got any other idea i don´t know.<br>
<br>
To define a part of a zone for no coh you need the x/y - coordinates for the object (for example the Inner Arx) relative to the zone + z-coordianate to determine if the non coh. That´s of course a very simple for just a ONE point.<br>
